    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-06-18T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-06-18T14:00:00-05:00" n="667"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d667">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">816.00/879: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Donald</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-18T13:00:00-06:00"
                            >June 18, 1932—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 5:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>50. Your circular June 17, 6 p.m. My impression of reaction in Guatemala to
                        <persName corresp="#p_MH1">Martínez</persName> manifesto is that it is felt
                    that <persName corresp="#p_MH1">Martínez</persName> has put something over on
                    the United States; that it is an extremely bad precedent and would very probably
                    raise similar ambitions in other malcontents. Previous conversations with the
                    Minister for Foreign Affairs lead me to believe the Guatemalan Government views
                    the situation with concern and believes a stronger policy advisable, at least to
                    the extent of closing the Legation. The Minister even hinted that an economic
                    boycott would bring <persName corresp="#p_MH1">Martínez</persName> to terms in
                    short order.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Donald</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
